@node FAQ.Storage.1.01 "Storage Questions 0.170"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.01 Why does the Amiga come with so little RAM or disk space?

            The Amiga requires less RAM and disk space than other computers.
        It is possible to use the Amiga operating system with less than
        20k of disk space and less than 100k of RAM. It is possible to
        run most Amiga software with 1 megabyte of RAM and one floppy
        drive.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Storage.1.02 "Storage Questions 0.262"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.02 Can I use IBM or Macintosh peripherals?

            Most external IBM and Macintosh peripherals may be used.
        Some Macintosh external peripherals may require additional
        hardware or an emulator. Many internal IBM peripherals can
        also be used with a bridgeboard or the Golden Gate II bridge
        card. In general, any storage device such as a hard drive or
        tape drive will work. High density floppy drives require a
        special driver which is freely available.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Storage.1.03 "Storage Questions 0.282"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.03 What is the difference between a Volume and a Device?

            A device is a name of a physical piece of computer hardware
        accessible by the system. A Volume name is a software based name
        asigned to that device. Provided are some examples which you may
        be using.

                     DEVICE              VOLUME

                     AMAX0:              AMax_System:
                     DF0:                Empty:
                     DH0:                Work:
                     RAM:                Ram Disk:
                     WB_2.X:             System2.x:
                     XH0:                XFH_Work:

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


