@node FAQ.Storage.1.05 "Storage Questions 0.282"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.05 What type of storage device should I buy?

                                    WRITE SPEEDｹ   SIZE     PORTABLE
            CD ROM                          1       640         x
            Floppy                    x     2         2         x
            Floptical                 x     3        21         x
            Hard Drive                x     4      2048
            Magneto Optical           x     3       640         x
            PCMCIA                    x     5         4         x
            RAM                       x     5     UNLIMITED
            Removable Hard Drive      x     4       105         x
            Optical                   x     3       128         x
            Tape                      x     1                   x
            WORM                      xｳ    3       640         x

            SPEEDｹ is rated with 1 being the slowest and 5 the fastest.
            WORMｳ drives may be written to free space only once.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Storage.1.06 "Storage Questions 0.282"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.06 What does it mean to format a device?

            In order for a disk to be used by the operating system, it
        must be recognized by the system. This first involves determining
        what type of disk is available, and then matching it to a set of
        predefined specifications that describe how data needs to be
        stored on the disk. Different operating systems require different
        methods of storing data, so this is necessary. Also, newer methods
        are constantly being developed. Finally, once the disk is recognized
        by the system and understood, it must conform to the operating
        system's predefined structure. If it does not, the operating system
        will not use the disk until it has been formatted. Once formatted,
        the disk will be blank and will contain no information.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node FAQ.Storage.1.07 "Storage Questions 0.282"
@toc FAQ.Storage

    1.07 What does 'unformatted capicity' mean?

            Every disk has an unformatted capacity, which is the maximum
        amount of space available on the disk. However, operating systems
        do not necessarily use all the information on the disk. Some
        tracks are reserved for test tracks or other purposes and are
        generally not used to store data.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
